The Meta Insight

You originally framed markets as matching producers and consumers.

That’s correct, but at a deeper level:

Markets are distributed search algorithms.

They explore the space of possible solutions.

The Pantheon simply applies that search process to knowledge itself.

⸻

Final Thought

If the system worked well, its biggest impact wouldn’t be a single domain.

It would be bridges between domains.

The most valuable artifacts in the Atlas would likely be:
	•	translation engines
	•	cross-domain models
	•	structural invariants

Those are the tools that let knowledge move across boundaries.

